    "content": "<h1>AKRABATTENE</h1><p>The place where Judas Maccabeus destroyed the strongholds of the &quot;sons of Esau,&quot; who were causing trouble for the Jews (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc5:3\">1&nbsp;Maccabees 5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Macc10:14-2Macc10:23\">2&nbsp;Maccabees 10:14â€“23</a>). The phrase &quot;In Idumea, at Akrabattene&quot; likely refers to a northern Edomite area near Acraba (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt7:18\">Judith 7:18</a>). It was likely not an area in the Negev Desert as people used to think.</p>",
